<br>
My main point was a group with a slower might be able to take a mob every 4 minutes (for example, I know it would be more often). A very offensive oriented group should be able to take a mob every 2 minutes until they needed a med break, at which point they would med for approximately 2 minutes for each mob they had killed, making the number of kills equal in both groups. This is not how it is in reality, but how a balanced game would likely work in ideal terms. The question is, can we think of a way that would allow this reality, not just for us, but for all classes that are offense oriented? In my opinion high damage low hp xp mobs it would be as valuable to burn them down quick and med, as it would be to slow and then kill them in a constant stream of kills (each kill taking longer, but with less downtime). <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2818<br> <font color=#333333>(2/4/03 4:12:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8676.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Thoughts on DPS vs Slow</span><hr size=1> There is no way offense can compete with slow, except possibly Manaburn.<br>
<br>
When modelling fights, I keep coming across the formula:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Power = Hit Points * Damage Per Second</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
A 65-75% slow reduces the mob DPS to a third to a quarter.<br>
Or seen another way, it is equivalent to multiplying the main tank's hitpoints by 3-4 times, AND multiplying all heals by 3-4 times.<br>
In order for offense to be equivalent to that kind of slow, it would have to reduce the mob's hitpoints by 65-75% in a very short amount of time.  Only manaburn comes close.<br>
<br>
Slow is one of the most powerful abilities in the game.  It outstrips both healing and damage dealing.<br>
The only saving grace is that slows do not stack, while damage dealing does.<br>
<br>
It is futile to seek to make damage dealing comparable to slow.<br>
<br>
